          <h2 style="
              font-size: 24px; 
              line-height: 1.2; 
              font-weight: 400;
              margin-top: 2px !important; 
            ">
              Carney attacks Trump</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/mark-carney-wins-liberal-party-leadership-succeeds-justin-trudeau-prime-minister.png" alt="Mark Carney speaks after he won the race to become leader of Canada's ruling Liberal Party and will succeed Justin Trudeau as Prime Minister" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Mark Carney speaks after he won the race to become leader of Canada's ruling Liberal Party and will succeed Justin Trudeau as Prime Minister. Credits: REUTERS/Amber Bracken/Pool Purchase Licensing Rights</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Mark Carney has won the race to succeed Justin Trudeau as Canada’s prime minister. He secured a landslide victory in the Liberal Party leadership contest, winning 85.9% of the vote and defeating several candidates, including Finance Minister Chrystia Freeland. In his victory speech, <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-11-03-2025-h1-1-he-aimed-at-president-trump?source=website" target="_blank">he aimed at President Trump</a> by condemning new tariffs on Canadian goods and Trump’s remarks about making Canada the 51st US state.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5;filter:blur(5px);">Carney said, “In trade, as in hockey, Canada will win.” He vowed to maintain retaliatory tariffs until the US “shows respect.” He also pledged to secure the borders and attacked opponent Pierre Poilievre, saying that Poilievre's plans would leave them divided and ready to be conquered. Federal Public Safety Minister David McGuinty said, “embodies steely determination and competence to deal with some of these big issues.”</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
